# Costify — Web + Mobile Feature Parity (Mirror App)

**Web (`apps/web`) and mobile (`apps/mobile`) are the same application.** Users must have equivalent capabilities on both platforms. Shared logic lives in `packages/shared` and `packages/client-data`; platform-specific code is UI and storage only.

Complements `nextjs.mdc` (web) and `expo-react-native.mdc` (mobile). See `AGENTS.md` → *Paridad web ↔ móvil*.

## Architecture

| Path | Role |
|------|------|
| `apps/web/app/api/` | **Only** REST API backend (Vercel) |
| `apps/web/lib/` | Server auth, MongoDB, tenants |
| `apps/mobile/src/api/client.ts` | Mobile HTTP (`apiFetch`, Bearer token) |
| `packages/shared` | Domain, Zod schemas, calculations, CSV parsers |
| `packages/client-data` | Hooks, sync, persisted workspace (web + mobile) |

Mobile never duplicates API or business rules. It calls `EXPO_PUBLIC_API_URL` / Vercel API.

## Mandatory workflow for every feature

Do **not** mark a user-facing feature complete until all applicable steps are done:

1. **Shared layer** — types, calculations, parsers in `@costify/shared`; hooks/sync in `@costify/client-data` if needed.
2. **API** — route in `apps/web/app/api/` when server persistence changes.
3. **Web UI** — component/section in `apps/web/components/` (or app route).
4. **Mobile UI** — equivalent screen/section in `apps/mobile/src/components/` wired through `AppNavigator.tsx` (or tab navigator).
5. **Shell wiring** — expose hook methods in both `AppShell.tsx` (web) and `SettingsTab` / tab screens (mobile).

### Pairing map (keep in sync)

| Concern | Web | Mobile |
|---------|-----|--------|
| App shell / data wiring | `apps/web/components/layout/AppShell.tsx` | `apps/mobile/src/navigation/AppNavigator.tsx` |
| Settings sections | `apps/web/components/settings/SettingsView.tsx` | `apps/mobile/src/components/settings/SettingsView.tsx` |
| Product calculator | `apps/web/components/calculator/CostCalculator.tsx` | `apps/mobile/src/components/calculator/CostCalculator.tsx` |
| Register | `apps/web/app/register/` | `apps/mobile/src/components/auth/RegisterScreen.tsx` |
| Auth / admin-only | `/admin`, marketing pages | **Web only** (documented exception) |

When adding a new **Settings** section on web, add the same `SettingsSection` id, nav item, and panel on mobile in the same PR/branch.

When adding a **form field** (e.g. `posSku`), add it to both calculators and ensure `migrateProductInput` / save paths preserve it.

When adding **import/export** flows (CSV, backup fields), wire `onImport*` handlers on both shells.

## API & sync rules

- Schemas and types in `packages/shared`; validate in API routes.
- Sync/backup payloads must include the same workspace keys on both clients (`locations`, `sales`, etc.).
- Call out if mobile needs a **new APK** (native dep, env, or JS bundle not delivered OTA).

## UI conventions

- Mirror **Spanish copy**, validation messages, empty states, and subscription gates.
- Web: shadcn + Tailwind. Mobile: RN + `StyleSheet` + `@costify/ui-tokens`.
- Platform-specific UX is OK (e.g. `expo-document-picker` on mobile, file input on web) if behavior matches.

## Before finishing / opening PR

Answer explicitly in the PR or chat:

- [ ] Web UI implemented
- [ ] Mobile UI implemented (or N/A with reason)
- [ ] Shared/client-data updated
- [ ] Both shells wired (`AppShell` + `AppNavigator`)
- [ ] `pnpm typecheck` passes

**If mobile parity is missing, the feature is incomplete — do not merge.**
